2019-11-29 09:29:05 Jonathan Warburton <jonathan.warburton09@gmail.com> contrib/flo-bigquery/src/main/java/com/spotify/flo/contrib/bigquery/DefaultBigQueryClient.java v 8d82f16752e480154865fc73c65e9b8808ffa553

Reload BigQuery job after it is done in order to correctly capture errors.

In the case where a BigQuery job fails immediately (e.g. bucket does not exist in GCS) the job is never reloaded, and errors are lost.
In this case the job is treated as DONE, whilst the returned JobInfo may still report that the job is RUNNING.
By reloading the job after it is DONE, errors are captured and the true state of the job is returned from the library.

2019-11-12 15:05:36 Nelson Arapé <nelson@spotify.com> contrib/flo-bigquery/src/main/java/com/spotify/flo/contrib/bigquery/BigQueryOperation.java v b250270ce075c2afee8cfa05b07d73f3d2bf5c11

Make success hook public

As described in https://github.com/spotify/flo/pull/125 , the original
idea was to be able to write
final Task<TableId> task = Task.named("task")
.ofType(TableId.class)
.context(BigQueryContext.create(table))
.context(BigQueryOperator.create())
.process((stagingTable, bq) -> bq.job(
JobInfo.of(QueryJobConfiguration.newBuilder("SELECT foo FROM input")
.setDestinationTable(stagingTable.tableId())
.build()))
.success(response -> stagingTable.publish()));

But because success is package private this use case is only allowed in
the classes in the same package, like the unit test
